==1961 Team Players in the NFL== {|class="wikitable" width="80%" |- align="center" style="background:orange;color:blue;" | '''Player''' || '''Round''' || '''Pick''' || '''Position''' || '''Club''' |- align="center" bgcolor="" | Ernie Davis || 1 || 1 || Running Back || Washington Redskins |- align="center" bgcolor="" | Pete Brokaw || 8 || 107 || Back || Baltimore Colts |- align="center" bgcolor="" | George Francovitch || 10 || 131 || Guard || St. Louis Cardinals |- align="center" bgcolor="" | Gary Fallon || 12 || 157 || Halfback || Minnesota Vikings |- align="center" bgcolor="" | Dick Easterly || 14 || 190 || Back || San Francisco 49ers |- align="center" bgcolor="" | Bob Stem || 19 || 265 || Center || New York Giants |- align="center" bgcolor="" |}<ref>http://www.pro-football-reference.com/draft/1962.htm</ref>
Ernie Davis was the first black player to be chosen first overall in the NFL Draft.<ref>Sports Illustrated, October 13, 2008, p.24</ref> Davis was drafted by the Washington Redskins then traded to the Clevand Browns in the first round of the 1962 American Football League draft.<ref>Rockinâ the Rockpile: The Buffalo Bills of the American Football League, p.564, Jeffrey J. Miller, ECW Press, 2007, ISBN 978-1-55022-797-0</ref> Tragically, he would never play in the NFL; he was diagnosed with [[leukemia]] shortly before he was to enter the league, and died in May 1963, less than a year after his diagnosis.
==Awards and honors== *Ernie Davis, [[Heisman Trophy]]<ref>http://www.heisman.com/winners/hsmn-winners.html</ref>
